eureka_ml_insights.user_configs.aime module

This module defines pipeline configurations for running AIME benchmarks.

It includes classes for standard, year-based, and hybrid extraction pipelines. Each class provides a configure_pipeline method to define the data processing, inference, extraction, and evaluation components.

class eureka_ml_insights.user_configs.aime.AIME2025_HYBRIDEXTRACT_PIPELINE(exp_logdir=None, **kwargs)

Bases: AIME_HYBRIDEXTRACT_PIPELINE

Config for running AIME 2025 benchmark with a hybrid answer extraction.

This class inherits from AIME_HYBRIDEXTRACT_PIPELINE and modifies the data path to the 2025 dataset.

configure_pipeline(model_config, resume_from=None, **kwargs)

Configure the pipeline with a hybrid answer extraction for the AIME 2025 benchmark.
